# Fijian Design for New Pages

When creating or editing screens in `src/components/screens/`, use the shared Fijian components for visual consistency.

## Import from `../fijian`

```jsx
import {
  MasiBackground,
  FijianHero,
  FijianCard,
  FijianSectionHeader,
  FijianInput,
  FijianPrimaryButton,
  FijianLabel,
  Icon,
} from '../fijian';
```

## Component mapping

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Full-screen background (auth, standalone) | `MasiBackground` |
| Hero title (SURVIVOR 50) | `FijianHero` |
| Cards, sections, containers | `FijianCard` |
| Section titles | `FijianSectionHeader` |
| Text inputs | `FijianInput` |
| Primary CTAs | `FijianPrimaryButton` |
| Small labels (Fijian/English) | `FijianLabel` |
| Icons | `Icon` (Material Symbols) |

## Colors & utilities

Use theme tokens: `ochre`, `clay`, `sand-warm`, `earth`, `stone-dark`, `fire-400`, `torch`, `jungle-400`.

Tailwind theme utilities: `shadow-fire`, `shadow-fire-lg`, `drop-shadow-text`, `drop-shadow-cina`, `text-shadow-glow-fire`, `text-shadow-glow-torch`, `text-shadow-glow-win`, `animate-flicker`, `animate-float-up`, `animate-pulse-win`, `animate-bounce-in`, `animate-pulse-sync`.

## No hardcoded values

- Use theme tokens for colors — never hex/rgba in components
- For JS (e.g. inline styles): import from `src/theme.js` (`COLORS`)
- For CSS: use `var(--color-*)` or Tailwind classes (`text-ochre`, `bg-fire-400`)

